🌍 1. The Observable World (The Surface World)

The world humanity understands.

Earth After the Ingress

Human civilization survived the appearance of mysterious spatial phenomena known as Gates.

Major cities are protected by enormous defensive barriers while remote regions have become abandoned Gray Zones, where Gates frequently appear without warning.


---

The Hunter Economy

Modern civilization revolves around Aether Crystals extracted from dungeons.

Energy, transportation, communication, medicine and military technology all depend on dungeon resources.

Hunters are celebrated publicly but the industry itself is ruthless.

Low-ranked hunters and porters often live under crushing debt, making survival itself feel like an optimization problem.


---

Society

Hunters are simultaneously celebrities, soldiers and corporate assets.

Guilds compete like multinational corporations.

The media glorifies efficiency, discipline and measurable achievement while quietly treating emotional hesitation as weakness.


